Background Script: Use the background script to send messages to content scripts in all tabs.
chrome.action.onClicked.addListener(() => {
chrome.tabs.query({}, tabs => {
tabs.forEach(tab => {
chrome.scripting.executeScript({
target: { tabId: tab.id },
files: ['content.js']
});
});
});
});

BACKGROUND EVENTS:

1. chrome.tabs.onCreated.addListener
   When: A new tab is created (e.g., opening a new tab or window).

Use Case: Initialize UI or logic when a tab is created.

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.tabs.onCreated.addListener((tab) => {
console.log("New tab created with ID:", tab.id);
}); 2. chrome.tabs.onUpdated.addListener
When: A tab’s properties change (e.g., URL, title, favicon, or loading status).

Parameters:

tabId: ID of the updated tab.

changeInfo: Object describing changes (e.g., {status: "loading"} or {url: "..."}).

tab: Full Tab object.

Use Case: Track page navigation or update UI when a tab loads.

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.tabs.onUpdated.addListener((tabId, changeInfo, tab) => {
if (changeInfo.status === "complete") {
console.log("Tab finished loading:", tab.url);
}
}); 3. chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener
When: A message is sent to the background script (e.g., from a content script or popup).

Use Case: Handle cross-component communication (e.g., sending data between content scripts and the background script).

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender, sendResponse) => {
if (message.action === "fetchData") {
fetchData().then(sendResponse);
return true; // Required for async responses
}
}); 4. chrome.runtime.onInstalled.addListener
When: The extension is first installed, updated, or Chrome is updated.

Use Case: Initialize default storage values or perform one-time setup.

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.runtime.onInstalled.addListener(() => {
chrome.storage.local.set({ isEnabled: true });
}); 5. chrome.tabs.onActivated.addListener
When: The user switches focus to a different tab.

Parameters:

activeInfo: Contains tabId (the new active tab) and windowId.

Use Case: Update UI or logic based on the active tab.

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.tabs.onActivated.addListener((activeInfo) => {
console.log("Active tab changed to:", activeInfo.tabId);
}); 6. chrome.webNavigation.onCompleted.addListener
When: A navigation event in a tab finishes fully loading (including iframes).

Parameters:

details: Includes tabId, url, and frame info.

Use Case: Trigger actions after a page fully loads (e.g., injecting scripts).

Example:

javascript
Copy
chrome.webNavigation.onCompleted.addListener((details) => {
if (details.frameId === 0) { // Main frame only
console.log("Main page loaded:", details.url);
}
});
Key Differences:
onUpdated vs. onCompleted:

onUpdated fires for partial changes (e.g., loading progress).

onCompleted fires only after the entire page (including resources) finishes loading.

Permissions Required:

webNavigation requires the "webNavigation" permission in manifest.json.

tabs events require the "tabs" permission.

Let me know if you need further clarification! 🚀

```

┌──────────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────┐
│      Content Script      │          │     Background         │
│ (Injected into pages)    │          │      (Service Worker)  │
├──────────────────────────┤          ├────────────────────────┤
│ 1. Control Panel         │          │ 1. Message Hub         │
│    - Pause/Resume        │          │    - Listens for:      │
│    - Screenshot          │──────────▶   - "captureScreenshot"│
│    - Restart/Close       │          │   - "syncTrackingState"│
│                          │          │   - "postimages"       │
│ 2. Tracks Clicks         │          │                        │
│    (via handleMouseClick)│          │ 2. Tab Management      │
│                          │          │   - onCreated          │
│ 3. Injects iframe UI     │          │   - onUpdated          │
│    (appendCustomDiv)     │          │   - onActivated        │
└──────────▲───────────────┘          │   - webNavigation      │
           │                          └──────────▲─────────────┘
           │                                     │
           │                             ┌───────┴─────────┐
           │                             │    Server       │
           │                             │ (Localhost:3000)│
           │                             │                 │
           │                             └───────▲─────────┘
           │                                     │
           │                          ┌──────────┴──────────┐
           └──────────────────────────┤    chrome.storage   │
                                      │ (Syncs isTracking,  │
                                      │  badgeCount, etc.)  │
                                      └─────────────────────┘

Key Interactions:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A. User Interaction Flow (Content Script → Background):
   1. Click "Pause" → sendMessage("syncTrackingState")
   2. Click "Screenshot" → sendMessage("captureScreenshot")
   3. Click "Done" → sendMessage("postimages")

B. Background → Content Script:
   1. On tab change → sendMessage("initControlPanel")
   2. On tracking state change → sendMessage("updateTrackingState")

C. Storage Sync:
   1. chrome.storage.local updates → chrome.storage.onChanged
   2. Propagates state (isTracking/badgeCount) to all tabs

D. Server Communication:
   1. Background script handles POST/FETCH to localhost:3000
   2. Returns response to content script via messages

```
